# keys_duplicate_focus.scn — 活體牙 K2+K3: Cmd+D duplicate + F focus selection
#
# K2: Cmd+D duplicate (FactoryKeyMap.cs:14, TiXL: copy+paste in-place).
#   Selects node:2, presses Cmd+D, asserts Root children count goes from 6 → 7.
#   Undo (Cmd+Z) rolls it back to 6.
#
# K3: F focus (FactoryKeyMap.cs:13, ed::NavigateToSelection / NavigateToContent).
#   Visual change: the canvas viewport shifts. assert_diff confirms pixels changed.
#
# RED proof for K2: change child count assertion from 7 to 8 -> FAIL (only 7 after one dupe).
# RED proof for K3: change before_focus to after the focus -> assert_diff sees no change -> FAIL.

open app/testdata/compound_smoke.swproj

# Baseline: Root has 6 children.
assert_state '(.lib.symbols[] | select(.id == "Root") | .children | length) == 6'
echo baseline-root-has-6-children

# --- K2: Cmd+D duplicate ---
# Select node:2 (click its title strip).
do click @node:2^
assert_state '.selectedNode == 2'
echo node2-selected

# Capture canvas before duplicate.
capture full before_dupe

# Cmd+D = duplicate (Mac: io.KeyCtrl = physical Cmd).
do keychord cmd d
# After duplicate: Root should have 7 children.
assert_state '(.lib.symbols[] | select(.id == "Root") | .children | length) == 7'
echo cmd-d-duplicated-child-count-7

# Canvas should look different (new node appeared).
assert_diff before_dupe
echo canvas-changed-after-duplicate

# --- Undo one step (Cmd+Z) — duplicate must be rolled back to 6 ---
do keychord cmd z
assert_state '(.lib.symbols[] | select(.id == "Root") | .children | length) == 6'
echo undo-rolled-back-to-6

# --- K3: F focus selection ---
# Select node:2 again so NavigateToSelection has a target.
do click @node:2^
assert_state '.selectedNode == 2'
echo node2-re-selected-for-focus

# Capture canvas before focus.
capture full before_focus

# First navigate away from selection (zoom way out) so F has something visible to do.
# We don't have a zoom gesture yet, so instead deselect -> F -> NavigateToContent
# to verify F at minimum fires without crash and the canvas reacts.
# Press F with node:2 selected -> NavigateToSelection (frames around node:2).
do key f
# Give the animation time to settle (ed:: duration 0.3s).
wait 0.4
# Canvas should differ from before (viewport panned/zoomed to frame selection).
assert_diff before_focus
echo f-focus-changed-canvas-viewport

# (NavigateToContent leg dropped: needs a reliable empty-canvas deselect point, and
# F-with-selection above already proves the key fires and moves the viewport. The capture
# kind here is FULL (window incl. node editor) — `clean` is the Metal render output, which
# an unwired duplicate / a viewport pan never changes (first live run's lesson).)
